title.label: Foap - sell your photos - Foap AB
Great idea, if you've got a decent camera you'll do well

content.label: Great idea to build a stock image platform based on users photos. Not sure how much the average person will make but with a decent camera and the right photo - you should make a tidy amount of pocket money. Frustrating you have to go through such a long-winded process to upload one photo at a time. Also having trouble verifying who I am.

Think its a great idea. Do NOT like the verify yourself part as this gives too much personal info and god knows where it could end up. Sure it is legit but I wont be taking a risk. Also have waited 2 hours to upload 3 photos, and it just goes from 50% to 11% then 85% to 4%. Whats that about? Really needs updating and will be great

Restricted photo sizes,terrible community that rate everything low even though I've sold photos. Foap doesn't send the payment till the end of the month after you've sold a photo, if they even pay you I'm owed money and keep being told to wait.
This app has me hooked and has certainly got me interested in photography again. Loving the way it works and enjoying seeing other peoples photographs.
This is a great idea. A simple way to make money. Great app, well thought out. Works really well.

The app is ok but I don't like the fact some of the features don't work (like the "verify yourself"). 
I'm still waiting for improvements and the promised sells.

Don't use it enough!

But great to upload my photos for sharing the passion
Good social app for photo lovers. The app is a bit clunky but it is great place to share photos and improve your skills
For a newbie photographer like myself, you can learn a lot and get excellent feedback on your current work! Could do with category's for different ability levels and more missions running at once :)
Take some pics, post them, see if they pass a peer review ( couple of minutes usually ) and then you are published and ready to sell. Sold my first pic in a week - great fun and possible profit!

title.label: Great idea, good app. Hard work

content.label: The idea is there but it is a lot of work to get any of your pictures sold

It's a good idea and a well made app but not for people snapping pics on smart phones. Most of the pics sold look professional quality. At least shot on a decent camera. 
Good luck. You will need it!!

I enjoy posting my photos on Foap, but I think that you should not have to give your driver licence, or passport, to confirm yourself, I think that using a password should be sufficient, but please carry on, as you are.

Impossible to upload photos in the last two releases - photos stay stuck, get to 40% then regress again. No probs w internet signal on any apps (and downloaded updates no probs) - just a massive fail from the developers. Pointless.
Sold two photos, only get $5 each so I doubt it'll make me rich :-)
Fantastic app which encourages you to think why you take pictures beyond 'that's a lovely picture of my child'

It is ok , but I have lost trust after I did ask my friend to buy photo and no money was add to my acc... Even More , I have write to them I experience luck of understanding english and luck of professionalism after 10 letters ...The 1 man company solve my issue . Also there is little chance to sale photos . Other issue is Rating the photos - ppl manage to put in rubbish photos and get 2star for it and good photos will get 3 stars . There are some challenges you can take part in But be aware that sometimes description of the contest will not match the winning photo ...

It's fab for photo lovers as u can not only share your own photos but see the other people work and search by interest, & - you are in a chance of selling your photos; best to win the missions as they pay a lot more ;) I haven't sold yet, but I'm on it not for too long and maybe not a very good photographer :) seen some people that sold over a hundred photos on it!! But you have to upload stuff that sells than rather your life, but hey- it's hard to say what sells best (dogs cats and abstract)..

title.label: Goid concept but no money to be made

content.label: The app sounds good...you get money from taking photos, but there is literally like no chance your photo will sell.

title.label: Not good at all - security issues

content.label: At first this looked like a promising app, but since downloading it a day ago I've seen so many issues that it really off put me from using it. The last issue I've seen was really worrying, my profile photo was replaced by somebody else's mugshot. Who knows if my information doesn't show up in somebody else's profile?! Other issues:  verification doesn't work, not that I want to do that after today's issue, but when I tried it yesterday it kept failing and asking me to retry. Processing should take a few minutes according to the message, but it took a whole day for me. Couldn't delete photos from there and when refreshed it kept creating another copy I the same photo again and again. Review process is very inefficient, as other reviewer also said, how do people know what is a good photo? Will delete, waste of time.
Love this app, even made some sales! Thought it does keep crashing on the notification page and time is always listed as 'now'
Needs a lot more work, very laggy. Doesn't load up properly

I thought I give the app a 2nd chance after the 1st time it failed on so many levels, well has there been improvements? Yes it looks nice but editing your detail's to sell your photos, you might as well jog on as time after time the app fails to load the simplest of things like your location. oh and for identification it wants your passport of driving or licence details, as if I’m gonna store a document as important as that with them, yeah right get a grip.  So as quick as I retried the app it got deleted. If you want to sell your photos there are a lot safer ways and far more professional than this app as your photos are rated by its users, as if its users know quality images, some of my professional images got rejected over photos of kids pulling silly faces having a laugh…its the happy snaps of photo apps, don’t waste your time if your serious about selling your work use 500px or flickr.
I love this app. It's a great way to keep inspired if you're an amateur and even better...there's a chance someone will buy one of your photos :-)
This a perfect app for professionals and non to share photos, moments of their life and if u are really good u get awarded! This app has it all and it's really easy to use!
Magic!!!

It was ok until they started asking u to verify ure account & ure self with a scan of ure own driving licence .. Or passport.!! There is no way I'm giving that sort of information to an app. They have my email & also paypal information ... For which I've been paid twice for the sale of 2 photos of mine. But I'm going to delete this app now & revoke all my pictures unless they change the "verification" process.  Big brother is always watching & recording .... But please guys .... Don't abuse the fact !!!!
Really amazing looking at so many good pictures and being able to sell my own .waiting to see if I do sell any .
Thanks to Foap we're all professional photographers! Join the revolution.
Like the idea of rate other pictures and be rated. Some pics are awesome most of them just ordinary.

A good fun app, don't expect to make any money from it, some do, not many. I like to use it as an inspirational tool, gives me ideas to go out and use my camera as opposed to letting it gather dust. Seeing what others shoot is great as well.
